title.narrative: HO-Empower Youth for Work PMU HO-503001

description.narrative:
Empower youth for work is a project to create training, employment and entrepreneurial opportunities for young people aged 18-25, the majority of whom are young women, in poor rural communities affected by climate change in Ethiopia, Bangladesh, Indonesia and Pakistan.
This project will help young women and men living in poor, rural areas to earn a living, improve their chances of finding work and help their communities to adapt to climate change.
The IKEA Foundation is supporting Oxfam with a 18.7million euro grant over five years because it believes that empowering young people from poor communities to earn a living in a sustainable way will lead to better opportunities for them and their families.
The Project Management Unit for this programme is based at Oxfam Novib, The Hague: it is responsible for global project management and coordination, amongst other activities include technical advise, MEAL activities, research through the knowledge hub on governance and active citizenship, global communication and financial planning and reporting.

participating-org.narrative: Oxfam Novib was founded in 1956 as the Netherlands Organisation for International Assistance (Novib), and joined forces with Oxfam in 1994. Oxfam Novib is member of the Oxfam International confederation. Working together in the confederation, the Oxfam affiliates can speak with one clear and compelling voice on issues of global concern: climate change, health and education for all, agriculture, trade, and conflicts and emergencies. Oxfam Novib's main office is based in The Netherlands, it supports the work of a network of local offices, the implementation of global projects, fundraising, campaigning and advocacy. Oxfam Novib’s the Hague office contributes towards this project’s implementation.
